               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17300513-40-person260">
                  Alexander 
                  Hope 
               <interp inst="t17300513-40-person260" type="surname" value="Hope"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300513-40-person260" type="given" value="Alexander"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300513-40-person260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That he went to the Bank the Day laid in the Indictment to receive the Sum of 1400 and odd Pounds, that he apply'd to one Mr. Banks, a Teller, and gave him Effects for the said Sum; that he received a Bag with a 1000 Pound in Part, and he turn'd the Money out on the Counter, and as he was telling the Money, he saw a Stick in the Prisoner's Hand with a Piece of Clay upon it; that he catch'd hold of the Stick, took off the Guinea, and threw it to the Heap on the Counter; that the Prisoner was drawing away the Stick, and had separated the Guinea from the Heap about 5 or 6 Inches. He added, that the Prisoner being carry'd before Alderman Baylis, owned, that he had taken a Guinea in the same manner that he design'd to have taken that which he stopt him in taking.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17300513-40-person261">
                  Thomas 
                  Martin 
               <interp inst="t17300513-40-person261" type="surname" value="Martin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300513-40-person261" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300513-40-person261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That the Prosecutor coming to him with an order for 1400 l. he gave him a Bag of a 1000 l. and that telling it over again after the Prisoner's Commission of the Fact, there wanted just one Guinea.</p>
               <p>The Prisoner pleaded, That being under great Necessity, he did go to the Bank of England to get a Bill discounted, or borrow Money upon it, and being in much Distraction and Confusion, scarce knew what he did; the Jury found him <rs id="t17300513-40-verdict206" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17300513-40-verdict206" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of the Indictment.</p>
